fields.description:
Having a leading space in the %HOME% environment variable causes SourceTree to crash with the following error:

{noformat}
'git status' failed with code 128: fatal: unable to access 'C:\Users\<USER>/.config/git/config': Invalid argument (C:\Users\<USER>\<REPO>)
{noformat}

As highlighted by a customer in the following support ticket - [STSP-1447|https://support.atlassian.com/browse/STSP-1447];

Customer highlighted errors for the French translation in SourceTreeBelow;


bq. The "open in explorer" button in the commit panel is not translated in french. The correct translation should be "Ouvrir dans l'explorateur".


bq. Another translation issue is the "Push changes immediately to origin/master" should be translated to "Envoyer les changements immédiatement sur origin/master".

bq. The commit options dropdown looks really strange and should probably simply say "Options", "Options de la validation" or "Options de la commission" but the later ones looks really strange, i'd simply use "Options" as even the frenchies use Commit, at least thats what we do here in Quebec/Canada.

{quote}
All the options under the commit options look really weird. Following strings suggested;
"Amender la dernière modification"
"Ne pas éxécuter les hooks"
"Signer la modification"
"Créer un pull request"
{quote}

bq. You may see we are not using all french words as most developpers use anglicisms. Hooks are not "Crochet" in french unless you want the direct translation of "a hook" like in "Peter pan", "Pull request" has no equivalent in french too so would suggest just using Pull request!
